result.execSummary:
Travis Richard Plant was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Travis Richard Plant was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.descr: Records of prosec. are converted data. See file.

records.addlTxt: Letter to Governor of Wisconsin with Waiver of Extradition, etc.
Auth. copy of Waiver of Extradition forwarded to Governer Walker, Wisconsin.

Defendant Travis Richard Plant in court, in custody.  Jon D. Seifert appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant confirms he received a copy of Fugitive Complaint.  Warrant out of Dakota County, Minnesota.  Court explains Extradition process and advises defendant of rights.  Defendant willing to waive extradition, Defendant signes Waiver of Extradition.  Court finds defendant's waiver of extradition done knowingly & voluntarily and remands him to Pepin County custody to forthwith be delivered to accredited agent of the State of Minnesota for return to Dakota County.
